\",\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": {\n    \"emit\": true\n  },\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cli-codex\",\n    \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\",\n    \"reasoningEffort\": \"xhigh\",\n    \"serviceTier\": null,\n    \"sandboxMode\": \"workspace-write\",\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900,\n    \"requestedByFanout\": true,\n    \"actualDispatch\": \"direct-current-codex-agent\",\n    \"actualDispatchReason\": \"cli-codex SKILL.md self-invocation guard forbids nested Codex dispatch from inside Codex; this lineage records the requested executor and runs the loop directly.\"\n  },\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"fanout-codex-xhigh-1781514394068-103t44\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"allowedModes\": [\n      \"new\",\n      \"resume\",\n      \"restart\"\n    ],\n    \"deferredModes\": [\n      \"fork\",\n      \"completed-continue\"\n    ],\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n    \"label\": \"codex-xhigh\"\n  },\n  \"phaseExecution\": {\n    \"phase_init\": \"complete\",\n    \"phase_main_loop\": \"complete\",\n    \"phase_synthesis\": \"complete\",\n    \"stopReason\": \"converged\",\n    \"iterationsCompleted\": 6\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": false,\n    \"reason\": \"Fan-out leaf was constrained to write only inside the lineage artifact_dir; reducer commands resolve the parent spec research root and were not used.\"\n  },\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"initialized-then-status-updated\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"workflow-managed\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"generated\",\n    \"deep-research-findings-registry.json\": \"generated\",\n    \"iterations/iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"deltas/iter-*.jsonl\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research.md\": \"workflow-owned synthesis\",\n    \"recommendations.md\": \"workflow-owned deliverable\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":70,"totalLines":70,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/codex-xhigh/deep-research-config.json","time":{"start":1781519167156,"end":1781519167161}},"id":"prt_ecad12b4f001zLX3n3j6b1Xt0D","sessionID":"ses_1352f6392ffeYuDqFBXc7h0kg7","messageID":"msg_ecad11e7c001Jsu6ZtGt7pFeKd"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781519167870,"sessionID":"ses_1352f6392ffeYuDqFBXc7h0kg7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_MjzUmRDNxhfJQA2OkRX71729","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/codex-xhigh/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/codex-xhigh/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy - codex-xhigh Lineage\n2: \n3: ## 1. Research Topic\n4: Fable-5 efficiency: extract net-new fable-mode and opus-fable-mode mechanisms, map adjustable Public-repo surfaces by read reliability, and rank deduped surface x delta recommendations.\n5: \n6: ## 2. Known Context\n7: - Round 2 is research-only and must answer three pillars: extract net-new techniques, map adjustable Public surfaces, and optimize with ranked tier A/B/C recommendations. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/spec.md:77]\n8: - Round 1 already shipped the distilled Fable5 doctrine into root AGENTS/CLAUDE, constitutional rules, main-branch direct-push coverage, and sk-code baseline/blast-radius guidance. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/001-initial-refinement/before-vs-after.md:17]\n9: - No artifact-local resource-map.md existed at initialization, so this lineage emitted its own evidence map during synthesis.\n10: - Requested executor: cli-codex model=gpt-5.5 xhigh. Actual dispatch: direct-current Codex because nested cli-codex self-invocation is forbidden inside Codex. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/cli-codex/SKILL.md:17]\n11: \n12: ## 3. Key Questions\n13: - [x] What did round 1 already ship, so recommendations do not duplicate it?\n14: - [x] What net-new fable-mode-main techniques exist beyond the distilled Fable5.md doctrine?\n15: - [x] What opus-fable-mode mechanisms and metrics are portable to Public?\n16: - [x] Which adjustable Public surfaces are most reliable across OpenCode, Claude, and Codex?\n17: - [x] Which surface x delta recommendations rank highest by leverage / (cost + blast radius)?\n18: - [x] What runtime/protocol caveats must the merge agent treat as load-bearing?\n19: \n20: ## 4. Non-Goals\n21: - No framework edits outside this lineage packet.\n22: - No parent spec write-back, memory save, git staging, or hook installation from this fan-out leaf.\n23: - No re-recommendation of round-1 surfaces as if they were net-new.\n24: \n25: ## 5. Stop Conditions\n26: - Stop before maxIterations when all key questions have evidence-backed answers and residual novelty is below threshold.\n27: - Stop immediately if a needed write would escape the configured artifact_dir.\n28: \n29: ## 6. Answered Questions\n30: - Round 1 shipped the evidence/operations doctrine into root AGENTS, constitutional memory, main-branch direct-push, and sk-code. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/001-initial-refinement/before-vs-after.md:25]\n31: - Net-new fable-mode-main value is mostly ritual and operating method: mutation checks, adversarial review, cold-successor handoff, scar-tissue ledgers, and two-register work cadence. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/fable-mode-main/fable-mode-profile.md:113]\n32: - Opus-fable-mode adds a persistent governor pattern, UserPromptSubmit re-injection, and a transcript-based leak-test metric. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/opus-fable-mode-main/README.md:47]\n33: - Public's highest-reliability mechanism surface is the existing prompt-time hook/advisor bridge family because it injects compact context before the model responds across Claude, Codex, and OpenCode. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md:36]\n34: - Measurement should be first-class; the source metric names median words/message, tool:text ratio, caveat percentage, and self-opener percentage. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/opus-fable-mode-main/leak_test.py:13]\n35: \n36: ## 7. What Worked\n37: - Baseline/dedup from round-1 before ranking new recommendations. (iteration 1)\n38: - Treating fable-mode-main as ritual extraction rather than another doctrine dump. (iteration 2)\n39: - Mapping opus-fable-mode into setpoint/thermostat/measurement. (iteration 3)\n40: - Ranking by read reliability before surface preference. (iteration 4)\n41: - Making mechanism and measurement outrank more prose. (iteration 5)\n42: \n43: ## 8. What Failed\n44: - Nested cli-codex dispatch was not legal from inside Codex; the lineage records this instead of pretending provenance. (iteration 6)\n45: - Parent spec write-back and memory save would violate the artifact-only write boundary. (iteration 6)\n46: \n47: ## 9. Exhausted Approaches\n48: ### Re-recommend Round 1 - BLOCKED\n49: - What was tried: comparing round-2 scope against the round-1 before/after.\n50: - Why blocked: the spec explicitly asks for net-new logic and deduped recommendations.\n51: - Do NOT retry: adding the existing root AGENTS/constitutional/sk-code distribution as a new tier.\n52: \n53: ### Slash-command-only Overlay - BLOCKED\n54: - What was tried: using `/fable-mode` command style as the main mechanism.\n55: - Why blocked: the source itself says it is on-demand and session-local; Public needs persistent cross-runtime behavior.\n56: - Do NOT retry: command-only Fable mode as the primary recommendation.\n57: \n58: ## 10. Ruled-Out Directions\n59: - Re-recommend round-1's shipped set: already deployed. Evidence: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/001-initial-refinement/before-vs-after.md:17`.\n60: - AGENTS-only governor: decays in long sessions and lacks measurement. Evidence: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/opus-fable-mode-main/README.md:77`.\n61: - Capability-ceiling claims from prompt text: prompts steer style, not weights. Evidence: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/opus-fable-mode-main/README.md:81`.\n62: - Nested cli-codex provenance claim: self-invocation guard forbids it. Evidence: `.opencode/skills/cli-codex/SKILL.md:17`.\n63: \n64: ## 11. Next Focus\n65: Converged. Merge this lineage with the sibling lineage, then produce the packet-level `research.md` and root-level recommendation deliverable if the merge agent is allowed to write outside the lineage directory.\n66: \n67: ## 12. Research Boundaries\n68: - Max iterations: 10.\n69: - Completed iterations: 6.\n70: - Stop reason: converged.\n71: - Write boundary honored: lineage artifact_dir only.\n\n(End of file - total 71 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy - codex-xhigh Lineage\n\n## 1. Research Topic\nFable-5 efficiency: extract net-new fable-mode and opus-fable-mode mechanisms, map adjustable Public-repo surfaces by read reliability, and rank deduped surface x delta recommendations.\n\n## 2. Known Context\n- Round 2 is research-only and must answer three pillars: extract net-new techniques, map adjustable Public surfaces, and optimize with ranked tier A/B/C recommendations. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/spec.md:77]\n- Round 1 already shipped the distilled Fable5 doctrine into root AGENTS/CLAUDE, constitutional rules, main-branch direct-push coverage, and sk-code baseline/blast-radius guidance. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/001-initial-refinement/before-vs-after.md:17]\n- No artifact-local resource-map.md existed at initialization, so this lineage emitted its own evidence map during synthesis.\n- Requested executor: cli-codex model=gpt-5.5 xhigh. Actual dispatch: direct-current Codex because nested cli-codex self-invocation is forbidden inside Codex. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/cli-codex/SKILL.md:17]\n\n## 3. Key Questions\n- [x] What did round 1 already ship, so recommendations do not duplicate it?\n- [x] What net-new fable-mode-main techniques exist beyond the distilled Fable5.md doctrine?\n- [x] What opus-fable-mode mechanisms and metrics are portable to Public?\n- [x] Which adjustable Public surfaces are most reliable across OpenCode, Claude, and Codex?\n- [x] Which surface x delta recommendations rank highest by leverage / (cost + blast radius)?\n- [x] What runtime/protocol caveats must the merge agent treat as load-bearing?\n\n## 4. Non-Goals","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/codex-xhigh/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy - codex-xhigh Lineage\n\n## 1. Research Topic\nFable-5 efficiency: extract net-new fable-mode and opus-fable-mode mechanisms, map adjustable Public-repo surfaces by read reliability, and rank deduped surface x delta recommendations.\n\n## 2. Known Context\n- Round 2 is research-only and must answer three pillars: extract net-new techniques, map adjustable Public surfaces, and optimize with ranked tier A/B/C recommendations. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/spec.md:77]\n- Round 1 already shipped the distilled Fable5 doctrine into root AGENTS/CLAUDE, constitutional rules, main-branch direct-push coverage, and sk-code baseline/blast-radius guidance. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/001-initial-refinement/before-vs-after.md:17]\n- No artifact-local resource-map.md existed at initialization, so this lineage emitted its own evidence map during synthesis.\n- Requested executor: cli-codex model=gpt-5.5 xhigh. Actual dispatch: direct-current Codex because nested cli-codex self-invocation is forbidden inside Codex. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/cli-codex/SKILL.md:17]\n\n## 3. Key Questions\n- [x] What did round 1 already ship, so recommendations do not duplicate it?\n- [x] What net-new fable-mode-main techniques exist beyond the distilled Fable5.md doctrine?\n- [x] What opus-fable-mode mechanisms and metrics are portable to Public?\n- [x] Which adjustable Public surfaces are most reliable across OpenCode, Claude, and Codex?\n- [x] Which surface x delta recommendations rank highest by leverage / (cost + blast radius)?\n- [x] What runtime/protocol caveats must the merge agent treat as load-bearing?\n\n## 4. Non-Goals\n- No framework edits outside this lineage packet.\n- No parent spec write-back, memory save, git staging, or hook installation from this fan-out leaf.\n- No re-recommendation of round-1 surfaces as if they were net-new.\n\n## 5. Stop Conditions\n- Stop before maxIterations when all key questions have evidence-backed answers and residual novelty is below threshold.\n- Stop immediately if a needed write would escape the configured artifact_dir.\n\n## 6. Answered Questions\n- Round 1 shipped the evidence/operations doctrine into root AGENTS, constitutional memory, main-branch direct-push, and sk-code. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/001-initial-refinement/before-vs-after.md:25]\n- Net-new fable-mode-main value is mostly ritual and operating method: mutation checks, adversarial review, cold-successor handoff, scar-tissue ledgers, and two-register work cadence. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/fable-mode-main/fable-mode-profile.md:113]\n- Opus-fable-mode adds a persistent governor pattern, UserPromptSubmit re-injection, and a transcript-based leak-test metric. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/opus-fable-mode-main/README.md:47]\n- Public's highest-reliability mechanism surface is the existing prompt-time hook/advisor bridge family because it injects compact context before the model responds across Claude, Codex, and OpenCode. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md:36]\n- Measurement should be first-class; the source metric names median words/message, tool:text ratio, caveat percentage, and self-opener percentage. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/opus-fable-mode-main/leak_test.py:13]\n\n## 7. What Worked\n- Baseline/dedup from round-1 before ranking new recommendations. (iteration 1)\n- Treating fable-mode-main as ritual extraction rather than another doctrine dump. (iteration 2)\n- Mapping opus-fable-mode into setpoint/thermostat/measurement. (iteration 3)\n- Ranking by read reliability before surface preference. (iteration 4)\n- Making mechanism and measurement outrank more prose. (iteration 5)\n\n## 8. What Failed\n- Nested cli-codex dispatch was not legal from inside Codex; the lineage records this instead of pretending provenance. (iteration 6)\n- Parent spec write-back and memory save would violate the artifact-only write boundary. (iteration 6)\n\n## 9. Exhausted Approaches\n### Re-recommend Round 1 - BLOCKED\n- What was tried: comparing round-2 scope against the round-1 before/after.\n- Why blocked: the spec explicitly asks for net-new logic and deduped recommendations.\n- Do NOT retry: adding the existing root AGENTS/constitutional/sk-code distribution as a new tier.\n\n### Slash-command-only Overlay - BLOCKED\n- What was tried: using `/fable-mode` command style as the main mechanism.\n- Why blocked: the source itself says it is on-demand and session-local; Public needs persistent cross-runtime behavior.\n- Do NOT retry: command-only Fable mode as the primary recommendation.\n\n## 10. Ruled-Out Directions\n- Re-recommend round-1's shipped set: already deployed. Evidence: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/001-initial-refinement/before-vs-after.md:17`.\n- AGENTS-only governor: decays in long sessions and lacks measurement. Evidence: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/opus-fable-mode-main/README.md:77`.\n- Capability-ceiling claims from prompt text: prompts steer style, not weights. Evidence: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/opus-fable-mode-main/README.md:81`.\n- Nested cli-codex provenance claim: self-invocation guard forbids it. Evidence: `.opencode/skills/cli-codex/SKILL.md:17`.\n\n## 11. Next Focus\nConverged. Merge this lineage with the sibling lineage, then produce the packet-level `research.md` and root-level recommendation deliverable if the merge agent is allowed to write outside the lineage directory.\n\n## 12. Research Boundaries\n- Max iterations: 10.\n- Completed iterations: 6.\n- Stop reason: converged.\n- Write boundary honored: lineage artifact_dir only.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":71,"totalLines":71,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/codex-xhigh/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1781519167865,"end":1781519167869}},"id":"prt_ecad12edd001dlawEXDi1qJESV","sessionID":"ses_1352f6392ffeYuDqFBXc7h0kg7","messageID":"msg_ecad11e7c001Jsu6ZtGt7pFeKd"}}
