\":\"insight\",\"focus\":\"Rank surface x delta recommendations by leverage, cost, blast radius, and dedup status.\",\"findingsCount\":9,\"newInfoRatio\":0.24,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Most evidence was confirmatory, but the ranking insight is new: mechanism and measurement outrank more doctrine text for round 2.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"What should be recommended first?\",\"What is deduped against round 1?\",\"Which tier owns each delta?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"What should be recommended first?\",\"What is deduped against round 1?\",\"Which tier owns each delta?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Put the behavioral governor only in AGENTS.md\",\"reason\":\"AGENTS.md is already dense and read once; the Opus source says a memory line decays and needs per-prompt re-injection.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/opus-fable-mode-main/README.md:77\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-15T09:10:45Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-codex-xhigh-1781514394068-103t44\",\"generation\":1}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":6,\"run\":6,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Validate convergence, document runtime caveats, and finalize synthesis.\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.04,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Only residual novelty remained: executor-provenance caveats and final eliminated alternatives; all key questions had evidence-backed answers.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"What runtime caveats must be flagged?\",\"Can this lineage converge before maxIterations?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"What runtime caveats must be flagged?\",\"Can this lineage converge before maxIterations?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Claim this lineage actually spawned nested cli-codex gpt-5.5 processes\",\"reason\":\"The cli-codex skill forbids self-invocation from inside Codex; the requested executor is recorded, but actual execution is direct-current Codex.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/cli-codex/SKILL.md:17\"},{\"approach\":\"Run spec write-back or memory save from this leaf\",\"reason\":\"The fan-out instruction freezes writes to the lineage artifact_dir only; spec write-back and memory save would touch parent spec docs.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:906\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-15T09:10:45Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-codex-xhigh-1781514394068-103t44\",\"generation\":1}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":6,\"answeredCount\":6,\"totalQuestions\":6,\"stopReason\":\"converged\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-15T09:10:45Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-codex-xhigh-1781514394068-103t44\",\"generation\":1}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/codex-xhigh/deep-research-state.jsonl","text":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Fable-5 efficiency: extract net-new fable-mode and opus-fable-mode mechanisms, map adjustable Public-repo surfaces by read reliability, and rank deduped surface x delta recommendations.\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-15T09:10:45Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/codex-xhigh\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-codex-xhigh-1781514394068-103t44\",\"generation\":1}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Initialize the charter and dedupe against round-1 shipped doctrine.\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.92,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First pass established the baseline doctrine, the round-1 shipped set, and the net-new gap taxonomy.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"What did round 1 already ship?\",\"What is the source baseline?\",\"Which risks constrain this lineage?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"What did round 1 already ship?\",\"What is the source baseline?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Re-recommend the round-1 AGENTS/constitutional/sk-code distribution as the main deliverable\",\"reason\":\"Round 1 already shipped those surfaces; round 2 must focus on net-new mechanisms and measurement.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/001-initial-refinement/before-vs-after.md:17\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-15T09:10:45Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-codex-xhigh-1781514394068-103t44\",\"generation\":1}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"run\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Extract net-new techniques from fable-mode-main profile and command overlay.\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.78,\"noveltyJustification\":\"The profile adds rituals and failure modes not present in the distilled Fable5.md note: mutation checks, adversarial review, scar-tissue handoffs, and two-register operation.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Which fable-mode-main techniques are net-new versus Fable5.md?\",\"Which techniques are doctrine, ritual, mechanism, or measurement?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Which fable-mode-main techniques are net-new versus Fable5.md?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Install a slash-command-only fable mode as the primary Public mechanism\",\"reason\":\"The source command is on-demand and session-local; Public needs persistent cross-runtime influence for default behavior.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/fable-mode-main/README.md:3\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-15T09:10:45Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-codex-xhigh-1781514394068-103t44\",\"generation\":1}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Extract opus-fable-mode governor, re-injection, and measurement mechanisms.\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.61,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This pass converted the Opus source into concrete mechanism and metric candidates: setpoint, thermostat, and leak-test measurement.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Which opus-fable-mode mechanisms are portable?\",\"Which metrics can verify behavioral movement?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Which opus-fable-mode mechanisms are portable?\",\"Which metrics can verify behavioral movement?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Treat prompt text as a capability upgrade\",\"reason\":\"The source explicitly says prompts steer working style but do not change the model's capability ceiling.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/external/opus-fable-mode-main/README.md:7\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-15T09:10:45Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-codex-xhigh-1781514394068-103t44\",\"generation\":1}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":4,\"run\":4,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Map adjustable Public surfaces by read reliability and runtime reach.\",\"findingsCount\":8,\"newInfoRatio\":0.43,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Surface inventory found the strongest persistent mechanism: prompt-time hooks and advisor bridge, plus lower-reliability skill, agent, and command surfaces.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Which surfaces are adjustable?\",\"Which surfaces have high read reliability per runtime?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Which surfaces are adjustable?\",\"Which surfaces have high read reliability per runtime?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Scatter new doctrine across every agent and command first\",\"reason\":\"Agent and command files are narrower and more drift-prone than always-read root instructions and prompt-time hook injection.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/skill_advis