{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781519664522,"sessionID":"ses_1352f6392ffeYuDqFBXc7h0kg7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_do0ZTKOK4TYGA0tnjwqr9560","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy - deepseek-v4-pro Lineage\n2: \n3: ## 1. Research Topic\n4: Fable-5 efficiency: map every adjustable Public-repo surface and optimization by independently extracting net-new techniques from `fable-mode-main/` and `opus-fable-mode-main/`, mapping surfaces by read-reliability per runtime, and producing a ranked, tiered, deduped recommendation set. This is the third independent lineage (after codex-xhigh=gpt-5.5 and opus-account2=claude-opus-4-8), bringing a non-Anthropic model's assessment of what is genuinely portable vs source-model-specific.\n5: \n6: ## 2. Known Context\n7: - Round 1 shipped the distilled `Fable5.md` doctrine: AGENTS.md Operating Discipline subsection (9 bullets), 2 new constitutional rules, main-branch-direct-push fold, sk-code baseline/verification line. [SOURCE: 001-initial-refinement/before-vs-after.md:17-25]\n8: - Round 2 scope is research-only: three pillars (EXTRACT, SURFACE MAP, OPTIMIZE) over two new sources — `external/fable-mode-main/` (62KB forensic profile + `/fable-mode` command) and `external/opus-fable-mode-main/` (governor, UserPromptSubmit hook, leak_test.py measurement, CLAUDE.md). [SOURCE: 002/spec.md:77]\n9: - Two sibling lineages already completed: codex-xhigh (6 iters, converged) and opus-account2 (5 iters, maxIterationsReached). Both independently converged on: (a) governor-on-hook as the highest-leverage mechanism, (b) mutation-check discipline in sk-code, (c) leak-test-style measurement, (d) recursion-control for anxiety models, (e) executor-provenance fail-loud hardening. [SOURCE: codex-xhigh/deep-research-strategy.md:56-66; opus-account2/research.md:12-14]\n10: - This lineage's unique contribution: assess what is genuinely *portable* (model-agnostic) vs what is *Anthropic-specific* (governor grammar tuned to Opus's anxiety texture, CLAUDE.md-only hook wiring, log paths under `~/.claude/projects`). DeepSeek's architecture differs — the recursion-control rule aimed at Opus self-audit loops may not map 1:1, and different models have different efficiency pathologies.\n11: - No artifact-local resource-map.md existed at init; this lineage emits its own during synthesis.\n12: - Write boundary: lineage artifact_dir only. No parent spec write-back, memory save, or hook installation.\n13: \n14: ## 3. Key Questions\n15: - [ ] Q1: Which fable-mode and opus-fable-mode techniques are genuinely model-agnostic (portable) vs Anthropic-model-specific?\n16: - [ ] Q2: Does the surface read-reliability map hold when assessed from a non-Claude, non-OpenAI model perspective?\n17: - [ ] Q3: Which recommendations from the sibling lineages converge independently, and where does this lineage diverge?\n18: - [ ] Q4: Are there leverage opportunities the Anthropic-model lineages missed because they operate inside the source ecosystem?\n19: - [ ] Q5: Which mechanisms can be enforced structurally (executor-config / post-dispatch-validate / renderPromptPack) rather than relying on prompt-time persuasion?\n20: \n21: ## 4. Non-Goals\n22: - No framework edits outside this lineage packet.\n23: - No parent spec write-back, memory save, git staging, or hook installation.\n24: - No re-recommendation of round-1's shipped set.\n25: - No claim that DeepSeek's assessment of Anthropic-model-specific behaviors is authoritative over the Anthropic lineages' own assessment.\n26: \n27: ## 5. Stop Conditions\n28: - Stop before maxIterations when all key questions have evidence-backed answers and residual novelty is below threshold.\n29: - Stop immediately if a needed write would escape the configured artifact_dir.\n30: - Stop if both sibling lineages' core findings are independently confirmed (convergence-with-consensus is a valid stop).\n31: - Max 5 iterations per config.\n32: \n33: ## 6. Answered Questions\n34: *(populated by iterations)*\n35: \n36: ## 7. What Worked\n37: *(populated by iterations)*\n38: \n39: ## 8. What Failed\n40: *(populated by iterations)*\n41: \n42: ## 9. Exhausted Approaches\n43: *(populated by iterations)*\n44: \n45: ## 10. Ruled-Out Directions\n46: *(populated by iterations)*\n47: \n48: ## 11. Next Focus\n49: Iteration 1: Initialize the charter, verify round-1 shipped set by reading the before-vs-after, establish the source baseline, and identify net-new vs known-gap distinctions. Focus on the portability question (Q1).\n50: \n51: ## 12. Research Boundaries\n52: - Max iterations: 5.\n53: - Write boundary: lineage artifact_dir only.\n54: - Sibling lineages available for cross-reference but not as primary sources.\n\n(End of file - total 54 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy - deepseek-v4-pro Lineage\n\n## 1. Research Topic\nFable-5 efficiency: map every adjustable Public-repo surface and optimization by independently extracting net-new techniques from `fable-mode-main/` and `opus-fable-mode-main/`, mapping surfaces by read-reliability per runtime, and producing a ranked, tiered, deduped recommendation set. This is the third independent lineage (after codex-xhigh=gpt-5.5 and opus-account2=claude-opus-4-8), bringing a non-Anthropic model's assessment of what is genuinely portable vs source-model-specific.\n\n## 2. Known Context\n- Round 1 shipped the distilled `Fable5.md` doctrine: AGENTS.md Operating Discipline subsection (9 bullets), 2 new constitutional rules, main-branch-direct-push fold, sk-code baseline/verification line. [SOURCE: 001-initial-refinement/before-vs-after.md:17-25]\n- Round 2 scope is research-only: three pillars (EXTRACT, SURFACE MAP, OPTIMIZE) over two new sources — `external/fable-mode-main/` (62KB forensic profile + `/fable-mode` command) and `external/opus-fable-mode-main/` (governor, UserPromptSubmit hook, leak_test.py measurement, CLAUDE.md). [SOURCE: 002/spec.md:77]\n- Two sibling lineages already completed: codex-xhigh (6 iters, converged) and opus-account2 (5 iters, maxIterationsReached). Both independently converged on: (a) governor-on-hook as the highest-leverage mechanism, (b) mutation-check discipline in sk-code, (c) leak-test-style measurement, (d) recursion-control for anxiety models, (e) executor-provenance fail-loud hardening. [SOURCE: codex-xhigh/deep-research-strategy.md:56-66; opus-account2/research.md:12-14]\n- This lineage's unique contribution: assess what is genuinely *portable* (model-agnostic) vs what is *Anthropic-specific* (governor grammar tuned to Opus's anxiety texture, CLAUDE.md-only hook wiring, log paths under `~/.claude/projects`). DeepSeek's architecture differs — the recursion-control rule aimed at Opus self-audit loops may not map 1:1, and different models have different efficiency pathologies.\n- No artifact-local resource-map.md existed at init; this lineage emits its own during synthesis.\n- Write boundary: lineage artifact_dir only. No parent spec write-back, memory save, or hook installation.\n\n## 3. Key Questions\n- [ ] Q1: Which fable-mode and opus-fable-mode techniques are genuinely model-agnostic (portable) vs Anthropic-model-specific?\n- [ ] Q2: Does the surface read-reliability map hold when assessed from a non-Claude, non-OpenAI model perspective?\n- [ ] Q3: Which recommendations from the sibling lineages converge independently, and where does this lineage diverge?\n- [ ] Q4: Are there leverage opportunities the Anthropic-model lineages missed because they operate inside the source ecosystem?\n- [ ] Q5: Which mechanisms can be enforced structurally (executor-config / post-dispatch-validate / renderPromptPack) rather than relying on prompt-time persuasion?\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy - deepseek-v4-pro Lineage\n\n## 1. Research Topic\nFable-5 efficiency: map every adjustable Public-repo surface and optimization by independently extracting net-new techniques from `fable-mode-main/` and `opus-fable-mode-main/`, mapping surfaces by read-reliability per runtime, and producing a ranked, tiered, deduped recommendation set. This is the third independent lineage (after codex-xhigh=gpt-5.5 and opus-account2=claude-opus-4-8), bringing a non-Anthropic model's assessment of what is genuinely portable vs source-model-specific.\n\n## 2. Known Context\n- Round 1 shipped the distilled `Fable5.md` doctrine: AGENTS.md Operating Discipline subsection (9 bullets), 2 new constitutional rules, main-branch-direct-push fold, sk-code baseline/verification line. [SOURCE: 001-initial-refinement/before-vs-after.md:17-25]\n- Round 2 scope is research-only: three pillars (EXTRACT, SURFACE MAP, OPTIMIZE) over two new sources — `external/fable-mode-main/` (62KB forensic profile + `/fable-mode` command) and `external/opus-fable-mode-main/` (governor, UserPromptSubmit hook, leak_test.py measurement, CLAUDE.md). [SOURCE: 002/spec.md:77]\n- Two sibling lineages already completed: codex-xhigh (6 iters, converged) and opus-account2 (5 iters, maxIterationsReached). Both independently converged on: (a) governor-on-hook as the highest-leverage mechanism, (b) mutation-check discipline in sk-code, (c) leak-test-style measurement, (d) recursion-control for anxiety models, (e) executor-provenance fail-loud hardening. [SOURCE: codex-xhigh/deep-research-strategy.md:56-66; opus-account2/research.md:12-14]\n- This lineage's unique contribution: assess what is genuinely *portable* (model-agnostic) vs what is *Anthropic-specific* (governor grammar tuned to Opus's anxiety texture, CLAUDE.md-only hook wiring, log paths under `~/.claude/projects`). DeepSeek's architecture differs — the recursion-control rule aimed at Opus self-audit loops may not map 1:1, and different models have different efficiency pathologies.\n- No artifact-local resource-map.md existed at init; this lineage emits its own during synthesis.\n- Write boundary: lineage artifact_dir only. No parent spec write-back, memory save, or hook installation.\n\n## 3. Key Questions\n- [ ] Q1: Which fable-mode and opus-fable-mode techniques are genuinely model-agnostic (portable) vs Anthropic-model-specific?\n- [ ] Q2: Does the surface read-reliability map hold when assessed from a non-Claude, non-OpenAI model perspective?\n- [ ] Q3: Which recommendations from the sibling lineages converge independently, and where does this lineage diverge?\n- [ ] Q4: Are there leverage opportunities the Anthropic-model lineages missed because they operate inside the source ecosystem?\n- [ ] Q5: Which mechanisms can be enforced structurally (executor-config / post-dispatch-validate / renderPromptPack) rather than relying on prompt-time persuasion?\n\n## 4. Non-Goals\n- No framework edits outside this lineage packet.\n- No parent spec write-back, memory save, git staging, or hook installation.\n- No re-recommendation of round-1's shipped set.\n- No claim that DeepSeek's assessment of Anthropic-model-specific behaviors is authoritative over the Anthropic lineages' own assessment.\n\n## 5. Stop Conditions\n- Stop before maxIterations when all key questions have evidence-backed answers and residual novelty is below threshold.\n- Stop immediately if a needed write would escape the configured artifact_dir.\n- Stop if both sibling lineages' core findings are independently confirmed (convergence-with-consensus is a valid stop).\n- Max 5 iterations per config.\n\n## 6. Answered Questions\n*(populated by iterations)*\n\n## 7. What Worked\n*(populated by iterations)*\n\n## 8. What Failed\n*(populated by iterations)*\n\n## 9. Exhausted Approaches\n*(populated by iterations)*\n\n## 10. Ruled-Out Directions\n*(populated by iterations)*\n\n## 11. Next Focus\nIteration 1: Initialize the charter, verify round-1 shipped set by reading the before-vs-after, establish the source baseline, and identify net-new vs known-gap distinctions. Focus on the portability question (Q1).\n\n## 12. Research Boundaries\n- Max iterations: 5.\n- Write boundary: lineage artifact_dir only.\n- Sibling lineages available for cross-reference but not as primary sources.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":54,"totalLines":54,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1781519664514,"end":1781519664521}},"id":"prt_ecad8c28d001TNWVSy87riMhkq","sessionID":"ses_1352f6392ffeYuDqFBXc7h0kg7","messageID":"msg_ecad8b5ba001jT2X1BJhfqyGxD"}}
